cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

This paper is about visual relationship detection, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper also involves language priors and semantic correlations, indicating that it may also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language). The proposed method involves a diffusion network, which is a type of deep learning model, suggesting that it may also fit into cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves graph-structured data, which is a common topic in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
